column10: Female driver in SUV failed to yield to pedestrian with crosswalk on at 4:54 PM from Prosperity turning right on Gallows.
Happens often at this crosswalk - people rarely stop for pedestrians.
At the SW corner of Lauren Elizabeth Lane and Gallows Road, a driver turned right with the crosswalk sign on.

driver failed to stop as i stepped in to crosswalk on District Ave- Intersection si 4 way stop and crowded with cars and people.Difficult for drivers to know when to go. Trafic light would be clearer.
Female driver didn't yield with pedestrian light on, and turned right into crosswalk at 7:27 AM
This crosswalk on Prosperity Lane and used by pedestrians going to Harris Teeter and the Metro, isn't at a traffic light, and is often ignored by drivers who don't stop when someone is crossing.

on Yates way. there is a cross walk down the street and up by the intersection but neither makes sense if you've parked your car in the deck and want to walk directly across the street.There needs to be a midblock crosswalk with flashers or a smart xwalk

On Saturday at 6:34 PM, I was crossing Gallows Road from Prescott Dr to Lauren Elizabeth Lane with the active pedestrian signal. A car on Lauren Elizabeth Lane turned right onto Gallows Road into the crosswalk when I hadn't finished crossing.
Driver made a rolling stop at the stop sign and drove into a pedestrian who was in the crosswalk. Pedestrian was fine.
